{
  "texts": [
    "First, it provides the model with the socio-demographic information of each persona it is supposed to simulate.",
    "Second, it conditions the LLM to select one of the expected answers suggested by the interviewer.",
    "On our data, we find this strategy able to make LLMs generate not only properly formatted answers, but also probability distributions that are both credible at first glance and varying over socio-demographic profiles.",
    "Here is an abridged example prompt foot_7:",
    "Question: What year is it?"
  ]
